  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6818.53 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6810 (-69.5B) and max positive gamma at 6830 (+40.1B), dealers are in active hedging mode - buying the dip toward 6810 and preparing to sell any push toward 6830. The massive negative gamma walls from 6800-6815 create a amplification zone where dealer hedging will accelerate moves, while the positive gamma at 6830 acts as the key resistance where dealers become sellers. The gex_surge event combined with the breakout regime suggests heightened volatility with 6810 as the critical support level - a break below triggers more dealer buying but also more downside amplification.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings between 6810 support and 6830 resistance with big moves if either level breaks.",
